THE celebrity chef, Lentswe Bhengu-Mafoko(37) has been described as a humble and passionate human being. On Wednesday, 1 March, Mzansi woke up to the news of the passing of the renowned chef. The cookbook author and TV personality died on Tuesday, 28 February, at the Sandton Medi-Clinic after suffering a short illness. While the family have said that Chef Lentswe died from a short illness, the chef did not hint at any signs of sickness on his social media timelines. 